main event: Unknown object detected by ground radar in Greenwich, Connecticut on 24 October 1962.
interesting points: The sighting lasted between 5 to 10 minutes., The object exhibited unusual and irregular motion not resembling any known aircraft., The radar recording indicated a steady course of the object., Visual contact with the object was not established., The landing was attributed to an A/P at Westchester.
sighted object: unknown object detected by ground radar
witness description: Lt. Colonel Joseph Lucey, Air Force
